able career which began as a swimmer atBarcelonain 1992, Storey further cemented her legacy in the eastern suburbs of Clichy-sous-bois.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 802, \"end\": 818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clichy-sous-bois\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ninth Games\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"a remarkable career\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"a swimmer\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"Storey\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"her legacy\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"the eastern suburbs\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 798}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She completed the 14.1km course in 20 minutes and 22.15 seconds, 4.69 secs ahead ofFrenchsilver medallist Heidi Gaugain, with Australian rider Alana Forster third.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\", \"score\": 0.9999999968515567, \"rank\": 3.132248163370139e-09, \"text\": \"Heidi\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\"}, {\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9997323815415159, \"rank\": 0.00026217309768069517, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._M._Forster\", \"score\": 0.9999998894793468, \"rank\": 1.105180210997983e-07, \"text\": \"Forster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._M._Forster\", \"dbpedia\": \"htt